    "body": "Newly implemented changing of language inside the app (https://github.com/streetcomplete/StreetComplete/issues/2643) seems to miss some places for localization, namely:\r\n\r\n- searching for quest name in quest descriptions\r\n- names of days in a week\r\n\r\n**How to Reproduce**\r\n- Compile/Install latest master (v38.0beta1 + fixed language crash bug), leave Android system language at default `English`, but change the in-app SC language to `Croatian`. Go into list of quests and click on magnifier icon to search by quest name. It seems to search using English, not Croatian (see video), even if Croatian description is correctly shown at the screen.  Exiting and clearing the app does not seem to affect this behaviour.\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/156656/142739300-43c50fab-1bdb-4e7a-ab11-9c95d0712764.mp4\r\n\r\n\r\n- Find `opening_hours` quest. Names of the days it shows are in English (`Mon-Sat`, `Sun`), while rest is translated to Croatian. Also when I goes to change the days, they are also shown in English.\r\n\r\n![small_Screenshot_20211120_203752_de westnordost streetcomplete debug](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/156656/142739031-49924412-c8bb-46f9-a4a6-678085d87cdc.jpg)     ![small_Screenshot_20211120_205820_de westnordost streetcomplete debug](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/156656/142739423-43e343c7-e00e-4bcf-a203-e9c949a6c60e.jpg)\r\n\r\n\r\n**Versions affected**\r\n\r\nStreetComplete `v38.0beta1+` (actually https://github.com/mnalis/StreetComplete/commit/2c130289d227bb943c25fdc4d50bbe31ff9c46b3) on Android 10\r\n",
